        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>ABLE Employment Flexibility Act</strong></p> <p>This bill permits employers to make tax-exempts contributions to ABLE (Achieving Better Life Experience) accounts in lieu of making contributions to existing tax-exempt defined contribution retirement plans. An ABLE account is established to pay the expenses (e.g., food, education, housing, transportation, employment training and support, and health care expenses) of a designated beneficiary who is disabled.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
